e, we also compute coronal\nfield lines extending to a few solar radii using a potential-field\nsource-surface (PFSS) model. Both the so-called type III-l burst and the\nmagnetic field configuration suggest that open-field lines extend from the\nflare active region into interplanetary space, allowing the accelerated and\ncharged particles escape.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 May 2013 01:14:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-05-27"}
